# ğŸŒ¦ï¸ WeatherAPI Frontend

This is a simple and straightforward frontend project developed to consume weather data from WeatherAPI and display the information clearly to the user.  
It was built using **HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript**, ideal for practicing API calls, DOM manipulation, and integrating external data.

## ğŸš€ Features:

* Search for any city entered by the user
* API call to retrieve:
* Current temperature
* Weather condition
* Weather icon
* Humidity
* Wind speed
* Graceful error handling (e.g., city not found)
* Simple, responsive, and clean interface

## ğŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used:

* HTML5  
* CSS3  
* JavaScript  
* Fetch API  
* WeatherAPI (real-time weather data)

## ğŸ“ Project Structure:

```
WeatherAPI-Frontend
â”‚â”€â”€ index.html
â”‚â”€â”€ style.css
â”‚â”€â”€ script.js
â””â”€â”€ README.md
```

## â–¶ï¸ How to Run:

1. Download or clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Gvnimra/WeatherAPI-Frontend

```

2. Open index.html in your browser
3. Type a city in the search field
4. See the weather displayed on the screen!

## ğŸ”‘ Configuring Your API Key:

1. Create an account at: https://www.weatherapi.com/
2. Copy your API Key
3. Open the file script.js
4. Replace "YOUR_API_KEY_HERE" with your key

